2
00:00:33.287 --> 00:00:38.203
<i>Episode 1: Magic</i>
<i>(or Something Less Assuring)</i>


3
00:01:05.662 --> 00:01:06.703
Really pretty!

4
00:01:07.245 --> 00:01:10.078
I like the eyelashes
reflecting the light.


5
00:01:13.495 --> 00:01:15.828
Let's try the hat.

6
00:01:24.537 --> 00:01:26.620
- There's something here.
- Thanks.


7
00:01:37.037 --> 00:01:38.745
Okay. Let me take a look now.

8
00:01:39.995 --> 00:01:41.620
Give us a minute, please.

9
00:01:48.495 --> 00:01:49.995
- Good.
- Yep.


10
00:01:50.162 --> 00:01:51.953
- They're very good.
- Yes.


11
00:01:54.912 --> 00:01:58.828
- I'm happy with these. You guys?
- Yep. Me, too.


12
00:01:59.037 --> 00:02:00.620
- Okay!
- Good job, everyone!


13
00:02:00.745 --> 00:02:02.328
Yay, we're done!

14
00:02:15.537 --> 00:02:17.495
- Thank you, bye.
- Take care!


15
00:02:17.745 --> 00:02:19.828
- Ride with me.
- Is it okay?


16
00:02:20.662 --> 00:02:22.870
- See you later.
- See you!


17
00:02:28.912 --> 00:02:31.328
- Take care.
- Thanks, bye.


18
00:02:44.495 --> 00:02:46.120
What?!

19
00:02:49.120 --> 00:02:52.495
You just met him!
How'd you click so well?


20
00:02:52.745 --> 00:02:57.245
Well, at some point,
he started saying...


21
00:02:57.787 --> 00:03:01.578
"Tsu, you're not
who I thought you were."


22
00:03:01.787 --> 00:03:02.870
"Tsu"?

23
00:03:03.037 --> 00:03:06.245
The bar owner suggested
nicknames for us,


24
00:03:06.537 --> 00:03:10.370
"Tsu" for Tsugumi, "Ka" for Kazuaki.

25
00:03:13.245 --> 00:03:17.453
So, I asked him
what he thought of me initially.


26
00:03:17.745 --> 00:03:20.828
He thought I was beautiful when we met.

27
00:03:20.995 --> 00:03:22.578
- Yup...
- Well, well...


28
00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:27.495
But he was under the impression
that I was aloof


29
00:03:27.745 --> 00:03:31.370
because of our email exchanges
before we met.


30
00:03:31.537 --> 00:03:35.328
That's the way business communication
should be.


31
00:03:35.537 --> 00:03:38.245
But you know how friendly I am.

32
00:03:38.412 --> 00:03:42.620
So, he was like,
"The contrast blew me away."


33
00:03:44.912 --> 00:03:49.495
Then I said, "Hang on.
You're a fine one to talk."


34
00:03:49.995 --> 00:03:52.370
Honestly, he seemed like a player.

35
00:03:52.537 --> 00:03:54.995
- A player!
- Well, not exactly.


36
00:03:55.245 --> 00:03:58.245
I should say, he's a hottie.

37
00:03:58.412 --> 00:04:02.578
- A hottie isn't the same as a player.
- I mean...


38
00:04:02.745 --> 00:04:05.828
He struck me as
a ladies' man at times,

39
00:04:06.037 --> 00:04:08.370
but not in a negative way.

40
00:04:08.662 --> 00:04:11.620
He says his home office is in Aoyama.

41
00:04:11.870 --> 00:04:13.120
That's players' haven!

42
00:04:13.287 --> 00:04:16.203
Hmm, I don't know about that.

43
00:04:17.037 --> 00:04:18.120
What does he do?

44
00:04:18.412 --> 00:04:21.870
He heads an interior design company
and invests.


45
00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:25.870
Now he sounds...like a player.

46
00:04:28.495 --> 00:04:31.620
Really, Gumi?
You don't like players.


47
00:04:31.870 --> 00:04:37.370
I know. I'm surprised that
I find his company so much fun.


48
00:04:37.537 --> 00:04:38.620
I see.

49
00:04:39.787 --> 00:04:44.120
I declined the business offer
and he accepted.


50
00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:49.328
But we kept chatting and
two hours passed before we knew it.


51
00:04:49.495 --> 00:04:54.370
Then, it went from "Wanna grab coffee?"
to "Do you drink?"


52
00:04:55.162 --> 00:04:57.370
And we missed the last train.

53
00:04:57.537 --> 00:05:00.245
Amazing. How long were you together?

54
00:05:00.412 --> 00:05:04.245
The meeting started at 1 PM,
so 15 hours all together.


55
00:05:04.412 --> 00:05:06.995
- No way!
- I know.


56
00:05:07.162 --> 00:05:10.828
Somehow, we started talking
about our childhoods.


57
00:05:10.995 --> 00:05:16.120
We found we had similar upbringings
and moved around a lot.


58
00:05:16.287 --> 00:05:22.370
We quickly realized that's why we both
approach people from a distance.


59
00:05:23.162 --> 00:05:28.495
I told him about things
I've never told anybody,


60
00:05:28.662 --> 00:05:32.703
not even to you, Meiko,
and he did the same.


61
00:05:33.745 --> 00:05:36.703
Maybe he was mirroring me to be nice.

62
00:05:37.995 --> 00:05:38.828
But...

63
00:05:39.662 --> 00:05:44.870
I could sense that
I touched something deep within him...


64
00:05:45.537 --> 00:05:50.245
and I felt he touched me
deep within, too.


65
00:05:51.245 --> 00:05:54.578
That sounds...erotic.

66
00:05:55.245 --> 00:05:56.828
Doesn't it?

67
00:05:57.162 --> 00:06:01.203
Honestly, I felt something
very erotic about it.


68
00:06:02.537 --> 00:06:07.078
I didn't know conversations
could be this erotic.


69
00:06:07.537 --> 00:06:09.328
- Did you talk dirty?
- No.


70
00:06:09.537 --> 00:06:12.453
No dirty talk, no physical touching.

71
00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:14.828
I don't get it.

72
00:06:15.037 --> 00:06:20.995
But we caressed each other
through our conversation.


73
00:06:21.370 --> 00:06:22.870
That's damn erotic.

74
00:06:24.370 --> 00:06:29.328
We ended up talking about
what we'd be like as a couple.


75
00:06:29.662 --> 00:06:31.870
- You guys are in love!
- I guess.


76
00:06:32.037 --> 00:06:35.495
We both sensed
we were falling for each other,


77
00:06:35.662 --> 00:06:39.953
or at least we got along really well.

78
00:06:41.412 --> 00:06:44.828
In fact, we thought,
we can do it.


79
00:06:45.412 --> 00:06:46.870
That's not dirty?

80
00:06:47.037 --> 00:06:50.620
No. Our talk flowed naturally
in that direction.


81
00:06:50.912 --> 00:06:52.120
You're so mature!

82
00:06:54.412 --> 00:07:00.620
But we were like, "Nah, not today."
So, we said goodbye and took taxis home.


83
00:07:00.787 --> 00:07:03.120
What? Why not?

84
00:07:03.495 --> 00:07:05.453
- No, no, no...
- No?


85
00:07:05.787 --> 00:07:07.745
Is sex on the first date common?

86
00:07:07.912 --> 00:07:12.745
I don't know, but in your case,
you could have.


87
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:16.245
Hmm, you're right about that.

88
00:07:17.037 --> 00:07:19.495
How about you, Meiko?
Have you ever...?


89
00:07:20.037 --> 00:07:21.120
What do you mean?

90
00:07:21.287 --> 00:07:23.120
Doing it on the first date.

91
00:07:24.245 --> 00:07:26.620
No, not the first date.

92
00:07:26.870 --> 00:07:28.370
The second or third time?

93
00:07:28.537 --> 00:07:30.328
Yeah, that happens.

94
00:07:31.245 --> 00:07:32.953
- Never done it?
- No.


95
00:07:33.120 --> 00:07:35.620
I can't. That's too fast for me.

96
00:07:35.787 --> 00:07:38.620
Most guys want it by the third time.

97
00:07:38.870 --> 00:07:42.703
I know. So, I put them in
"the players" basket.


98
00:07:42.870 --> 00:07:44.495
Gumi, you're harsh!

99
00:07:44.662 --> 00:07:48.745
- You and I are different on this one.
- Yup.


100
00:07:50.662 --> 00:07:52.828
To be honest...

101
00:07:54.787 --> 00:07:56.703
it wasn't a bad idea.

102
00:07:56.870 --> 00:07:59.620
I've never felt I could
on the first date.


103
00:08:01.787 --> 00:08:03.245
Actually, I wanted to.

104
00:08:04.787 --> 00:08:08.245
I wondered what we'd be like afterwards.

105
00:08:08.412 --> 00:08:10.745
If the convo was that good...

106
00:08:10.912 --> 00:08:15.370
I thought about consequences
and felt a bit unsure.


107
00:08:16.162 --> 00:08:19.245
But I think I was giving him signals.

108
00:08:19.787 --> 00:08:21.203
What kinda signals?

109
00:08:21.370 --> 00:08:22.995
I won't tell you. I can't.

110
00:08:23.162 --> 00:08:26.495
- Oh, c'mon!
- It just happened in that moment.


111
00:08:30.037 --> 00:08:34.745
You know...it was him who held back.

112
00:08:35.787 --> 00:08:37.703
He couldn't get it up?

113
00:08:37.870 --> 00:08:39.870
- Oh, shush!
- Ow!


114
00:08:42.870 --> 00:08:44.245
In a nutshell,

115
00:08:44.787 --> 00:08:48.120
he couldn't bring himself
to it mentally.


116
00:08:50.495 --> 00:08:51.495
He said...

117
00:08:53.787 --> 00:08:56.953
him and his ex broke up
because she cheated.


118
00:08:57.495 --> 00:09:00.620
Ah...that sounds familiar...

119
00:09:01.037 --> 00:09:02.953
Yeah, cheater! Apologize.

120
00:09:03.412 --> 00:09:06.620
Let us pray for forgiveness.

121
00:09:07.162 --> 00:09:10.995
And you know, he got cheated on
more than once.


122
00:09:11.287 --> 00:09:12.245
Uh-huh...

123
00:09:12.412 --> 00:09:16.995
But he loved her so much and

124
00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:21.495
it was so painful that
he probably can't love again.


125
00:09:23.287 --> 00:09:24.495
When did that happen?

126
00:09:24.995 --> 00:09:26.620
About two years ago.

127
00:09:26.995 --> 00:09:30.953
- He's dwelling on it too long!
- I know! But...


128
00:09:31.370 --> 00:09:33.745
I can empathize with that.

129
00:09:33.912 --> 00:09:35.245
I see.

130
00:09:35.495 --> 00:09:40.495
He also said he had lots of fun
with me but feels unprepared,


131
00:09:41.245 --> 00:09:43.495
this came out of left field.

132
00:09:45.162 --> 00:09:47.620
It excited him but

133
00:09:47.787 --> 00:09:52.120
it also made him realize
he's scared of falling in love.


134
00:09:53.912 --> 00:09:57.453
He said I reminded him of his ex.

135
00:09:58.037 --> 00:10:00.120
- You look like her?
- No.


136
00:10:00.412 --> 00:10:03.078
It wasn't my face or personality.

137
00:10:04.995 --> 00:10:07.870
But, he'd never...

138
00:10:08.537 --> 00:10:11.953
felt so at ease talking to someone.

139
00:10:12.370 --> 00:10:18.245
Then, he remembered that he was never
able to talk like this with his ex.


140
00:10:18.537 --> 00:10:20.953
Hmm...at ease...

141
00:10:21.662 --> 00:10:24.745
Yeah, it caught my mind,
so I said,


142
00:10:24.912 --> 00:10:28.203
"Feeling at ease isn't
the same as romance."


143
00:10:29.787 --> 00:10:31.203
What'd he say?

144
00:10:32.662 --> 00:10:34.120
"What do you think, Tsu?"

145
00:10:34.662 --> 00:10:36.328
How annoying.

146
00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:42.620
It's hard to explain the nuances.

147
00:10:44.662 --> 00:10:47.745
We spent a really magical time together

148
00:10:49.162 --> 00:10:53.328
and both felt we'd never
had an experience like it.


149
00:10:53.995 --> 00:10:59.203
He said that, for us who have
always kept others at bay,


150
00:10:59.620 --> 00:11:01.745
our paths crossing is special.

151
00:11:01.912 --> 00:11:06.120
And I knew that he meant
what he said.


152
00:11:09.412 --> 00:11:14.620
Then, he suggested we leave each other
at that and call it a day.


153
00:11:15.870 --> 00:11:20.995
He said, "If the magic is gone
next time we meet, then let it be."


154
00:11:21.662 --> 00:11:23.328
Magic, huh?

155
00:11:23.662 --> 00:11:26.120
The word was perfect for us.

156
00:11:26.870 --> 00:11:31.495
He said, "I honestly had
the best day of my life."


157
00:11:31.662 --> 00:11:36.120
"It'll be great if our next meeting
turns out even better."


158
00:11:36.287 --> 00:11:40.745
"I feel optimistic about us.
Let's hope we make it."


159
00:11:41.162 --> 00:11:42.870
Then, we shook hands goodbye.

160
00:11:43.037 --> 00:11:44.078
Seriously?

161
00:11:49.870 --> 00:11:52.495
Are you scared about next time?

162
00:11:53.745 --> 00:11:56.328
I am...very much so.

163
00:11:58.620 --> 00:12:02.495
And yet I want to see him. Soon.

164
00:12:07.412 --> 00:12:08.745
Gumi, you look lovely.

165
00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:12.120
You're glowing right now.

166
00:12:12.912 --> 00:12:13.870
Thanks.

167
00:12:20.912 --> 00:12:22.370
- Thank you.
- Thank you.


168
00:12:22.870 --> 00:12:24.120
Thanks a lot.

169
00:12:24.370 --> 00:12:25.703
- Good night.
- See you.


170
00:12:45.912 --> 00:12:47.245
Excuse me.

171
00:12:48.120 --> 00:12:50.828
Do you mind going back the same way?

172
00:14:28.162 --> 00:14:29.578
Is the president in?

173
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:32.620
- Pardon?
- May I come in?


174
00:14:33.787 --> 00:14:35.370
And you are...?

175
00:14:35.870 --> 00:14:36.870
I'm his friend.

176
00:14:37.412 --> 00:14:38.495
Excuse me.

177
00:14:39.787 --> 00:14:40.620
Yes?

178
00:14:42.912 --> 00:14:44.828
I need a word.

179
00:14:47.412 --> 00:14:49.120
Ms. Morita, you can go.

180
00:14:49.870 --> 00:14:50.703
But...

181
00:14:51.870 --> 00:14:55.078
I'll be fine. I
can do the rest myself.

182
00:14:57.287 --> 00:14:58.203
Sure.

183
00:15:07.745 --> 00:15:09.745
- Good night.
- Good night.


184
00:15:10.912 --> 00:15:12.078
Good night.

185
00:15:22.745 --> 00:15:23.620
Cute.

186
00:15:24.537 --> 00:15:25.370
What?

187
00:15:26.995 --> 00:15:28.620
You've moved your office.

188
00:15:30.495 --> 00:15:32.370
The old one was cute, too.

189
00:15:34.495 --> 00:15:36.370
Where's your bed now?

190
00:15:37.620 --> 00:15:38.745
Upstairs.

191
00:15:39.370 --> 00:15:40.370
I see.

192
00:15:41.245 --> 00:15:42.828
You look successful.

193
00:15:44.495 --> 00:15:46.370
What do you want to talk about?

194
00:15:47.537 --> 00:15:50.120
I heard you started investing.

195
00:15:50.870 --> 00:15:54.370
Can you handle that?
I never saw you as the type.


196
00:15:55.912 --> 00:15:57.203
Who told you that?

197
00:15:57.620 --> 00:16:00.370
You two spent a magical time together.

198
00:16:05.037 --> 00:16:06.453
"Tsu" and "Ka"?

199
00:16:07.412 --> 00:16:08.745
You guys are lame.

200
00:16:11.620 --> 00:16:12.870
You know her?

201
00:16:13.787 --> 00:16:15.120
You mean, Gumi?

202
00:16:15.745 --> 00:16:16.745
My best friend.

203
00:16:17.162 --> 00:16:18.078
"Gumi"?

204
00:16:18.912 --> 00:16:22.995
Because she's Tsugumi.
We had a shoot today.


205
00:16:29.245 --> 00:16:30.828
Are you surprised?

206
00:16:31.162 --> 00:16:35.995
Surprised? It's rather hard to believe.

207
00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:38.995
What's so hard to believe?

208
00:16:39.162 --> 00:16:40.995
She told you about me?

209
00:16:41.412 --> 00:16:42.745
Not exactly.

210
00:16:43.287 --> 00:16:45.703
I realized she was talking about you.

211
00:16:46.912 --> 00:16:48.495
Did you tell her about us?

212
00:16:48.870 --> 00:16:51.495
No, I didn't. How could I?

213
00:16:52.037 --> 00:16:52.870
Right.

214
00:16:55.870 --> 00:16:58.745
Are you in love with Gumi?

215
00:17:00.370 --> 00:17:03.120
- I don't know yet.
- How can you not?


216
00:17:03.912 --> 00:17:04.995
"A magical time"?

217
00:17:05.870 --> 00:17:08.370
"The best day of my life"?

218
00:17:08.620 --> 00:17:10.370
Hey, stop that.

219
00:17:11.287 --> 00:17:12.870
You think I'm jealous?

220
00:17:13.120 --> 00:17:14.703
- Aren't you?
- Not at all.


221
00:17:15.120 --> 00:17:18.245
I'm not at all
in love with you, Kazu.

222
00:17:18.412 --> 00:17:20.578
You've hardly crossed my mind.

223
00:17:20.787 --> 00:17:22.078
You got it easy.

224
00:17:24.162 --> 00:17:25.995
You passed yourself off as

225
00:17:26.412 --> 00:17:29.245
this traumatized guy who got cheated on.

226
00:17:30.537 --> 00:17:32.078
Did she say that?

227
00:17:32.495 --> 00:17:35.120
No. Partly my interpretation.

228
00:17:36.787 --> 00:17:39.620
Who are you to probe into that night?

229
00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:42.120
"That night"?

230
00:17:45.787 --> 00:17:50.120
Leave. You're acting like a stalker.
You're insane.


231
00:17:51.662 --> 00:17:52.495
Don't worry.

232
00:17:52.662 --> 00:17:55.995
I'm aware of my insane behavior.

233
00:17:58.870 --> 00:18:01.120
You're operating normally, then.

234
00:18:02.370 --> 00:18:04.245
- You know me.
- Why'd you come?


235
00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:06.245
Want to know?

236
00:18:06.662 --> 00:18:08.328
I need to. I'm scared.

237
00:18:09.745 --> 00:18:12.745
To tell the truth, I don't know.

238
00:18:13.537 --> 00:18:14.370
Huh?

239
00:18:14.912 --> 00:18:18.245
But there's nobody else
I can talk to about this.


240
00:18:18.787 --> 00:18:20.370
Not Gumi, of course.

241
00:18:21.162 --> 00:18:25.453
And I knew you'd listen to me
even after two years.


242
00:18:27.287 --> 00:18:30.078
- How have you been?
- Listen to what?


243
00:18:30.662 --> 00:18:31.620
I don't know.

244
00:18:32.370 --> 00:18:35.953
But you used to enjoy hearing
what I had to say.


245
00:18:38.995 --> 00:18:40.245
How've you been?

246
00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:42.578
What do you want to know?

247
00:18:47.745 --> 00:18:53.370
I got so pissed off when I heard
about you and her.


248
00:18:53.745 --> 00:18:54.995
I felt sad, too.

249
00:18:57.037 --> 00:18:59.745
But I'm not in love with you now.

250
00:18:59.995 --> 00:19:01.328
- And you...
- Don't.


251
00:19:01.537 --> 00:19:05.745
Maybe it's the loss of someone
I believed was mine.


252
00:19:05.912 --> 00:19:07.703
I don't belong to you.

253
00:19:07.912 --> 00:19:09.328
I'm talking about Gumi.

254
00:19:10.662 --> 00:19:13.370
Look, woman.
That girl's not yours, either.


255
00:19:14.537 --> 00:19:16.453
Why'd you just call me "woman"?

256
00:19:16.912 --> 00:19:19.370
You've never spoke like that to me.

257
