Maybe so. We both changed.

1034
01:27:34.287 --> 01:27:36.245
What do you do?

1035
01:27:36.537 --> 01:27:39.453
I'm a systems engineer. IT laborer.

1036
01:27:39.620 --> 01:27:40.995
So it means...

1037
01:27:41.162 --> 01:27:44.453
- Yup, I'm out of a job now.
- That's too bad.


1038
01:27:44.620 --> 01:27:50.578
But I have savings, and IT workers
get extra unemployment benefits.


1039
01:27:50.787 --> 01:27:53.078
I'll just take it as a break.

1040
01:27:53.537 --> 01:27:54.620
That's good.

1041
01:27:56.495 --> 01:27:57.870
Hello.

1042
01:27:58.620 --> 01:28:00.453
- Hot, isn't it?
- It is.


1043
01:28:00.662 --> 01:28:03.578
- Yu had fun at your home.
- I'm glad.


1044
01:28:03.745 --> 01:28:06.745
Hitomi can come play anytime, too.

1045
01:28:08.120 --> 01:28:10.453
Thanks, she'd love that.

1046
01:28:10.745 --> 01:28:12.245
- Good day.
- Good day.


1047
01:28:17.287 --> 01:28:18.828
It's kind of surreal.

1048
01:28:18.995 --> 01:28:19.953
Is it?

1049
01:28:20.245 --> 01:28:21.495
How old's your kid?

1050
01:28:21.787 --> 01:28:24.995
I've got a son who's 16,
and a daughter who's14.


1051
01:28:25.162 --> 01:28:26.870
- Really.
- Yup.


1052
01:28:27.537 --> 01:28:29.453
- Incredible.
- It's not.


1053
01:28:30.412 --> 01:28:31.328
Here we are.

1054
01:28:31.495 --> 01:28:33.620
Wow.

1055
01:28:43.745 --> 01:28:44.745
"Kobayashi."

1056
01:28:52.870 --> 01:28:53.870
Come in.

1057
01:29:01.662 --> 01:29:03.453
Put your bag anywhere.

1058
01:29:06.162 --> 01:29:07.870
Your partner...

1059
01:29:08.995 --> 01:29:10.495
What's his job?

1060
01:29:10.870 --> 01:29:14.370
He's an R&D in a pharmaceutical company.

1061
01:29:14.620 --> 01:29:15.745
Makes sense.

1062
01:29:15.912 --> 01:29:17.995
- What does?
- Nothing.


1063
01:29:18.620 --> 01:29:19.703
Any affects?

1064
01:29:20.162 --> 01:29:21.620
Of the virus?

1065
01:29:22.412 --> 01:29:27.328
His research data got leaked,
but so did other companies.


1066
01:29:28.162 --> 01:29:32.578
All he needs for work is the
microscope, so we're fine.


1067
01:29:32.745 --> 01:29:33.745
I see.

1068
01:29:34.495 --> 01:29:36.078
What'd you do today?

1069
01:29:36.745 --> 01:29:39.745
- I had a tea class.
- Really?


1070
01:29:39.995 --> 01:29:40.745
What?

1071
01:29:41.287 --> 01:29:46.870
Sort of unexpected, but I bet
you're cut out for tea ceremonies.


1072
01:29:47.537 --> 01:29:48.578
Thanks.

1073
01:29:48.912 --> 01:29:51.370
But I'm making normal tea for now.

1074
01:29:51.537 --> 01:29:53.495
I'm fine with it.

1075
01:29:55.620 --> 01:29:58.495
Want sweet bean jelly? I froze it.

1076
01:29:58.662 --> 01:30:01.245
- It's top-notch.
- You don't mind?


1077
01:30:01.620 --> 01:30:04.620
My family doesn't like it as I do.

1078
01:30:04.787 --> 01:30:06.120
What a waste.

1079
01:30:06.995 --> 01:30:09.078
Can I help?

1080
01:30:09.245 --> 01:30:11.245
It's okay. Just relax.

1081
01:30:17.995 --> 01:30:20.328
- Don't touch it!
- Sorry.


1082
01:30:21.037 --> 01:30:21.870
I'm sorry.

1083
01:30:24.287 --> 01:30:25.953
Is your kid a fan?

1084
01:30:26.162 --> 01:30:27.703
Yeah, my son is.

1085
01:30:27.912 --> 01:30:28.953
I see.

1086
01:30:29.120 --> 01:30:30.620
I'm embarrassed.

1087
01:30:31.162 --> 01:30:33.745
But anime these days are intriguing.

1088
01:30:33.912 --> 01:30:36.745
Today's package is
a Blu-ray for an anime.


1089
01:30:37.537 --> 01:30:41.370
Because all the VOD services
don't work anymore.


1090
01:30:41.662 --> 01:30:44.745
I missed the package two days ago.

1091
01:30:45.037 --> 01:30:47.578
My son gets cranky, you know?

1092
01:30:47.745 --> 01:30:49.203
Do you watch it too?

1093
01:30:49.370 --> 01:30:51.203
No. Do you?

1094
01:30:51.370 --> 01:30:53.995
I binge watch to kill time now.

1095
01:30:55.620 --> 01:31:00.370
I don't get it anymore.
Can't keep up with the conversation.


1096
01:31:00.787 --> 01:31:03.620
- You can, if you watch it.
- Maybe.


1097
01:31:04.245 --> 01:31:05.995
But I'm not interested.

1098
01:31:06.787 --> 01:31:11.245
I don't mind what people like,
but I'm not interested.


1099
01:31:21.787 --> 01:31:23.620
It's my mother-in-law's.

1100
01:31:24.037 --> 01:31:25.745
Oh, really.

1101
01:31:27.787 --> 01:31:29.620
You still play the piano?

1102
01:31:30.412 --> 01:31:31.203
Huh?

1103
01:31:31.870 --> 01:31:32.620
Not at all.

1104
01:31:33.537 --> 01:31:34.703
I see.

1105
01:31:35.245 --> 01:31:38.703
I only play for
my daughter's violin, too.


1106
01:31:41.620 --> 01:31:44.495
You seem to be scared of silence.

1107
01:31:44.912 --> 01:31:45.870
Do I?

1108
01:31:46.162 --> 01:31:52.120
You keep avoiding what's important.
Even though it's been 20 years.


1109
01:31:52.620 --> 01:31:53.870
What's important?

1110
01:31:55.120 --> 01:31:56.953
Are you happy right now?

1111
01:31:58.787 --> 01:31:59.745
Oh...

1112
01:32:01.620 --> 01:32:05.245
It sounds silly to ask
after seeing this house.


1113
01:32:06.412 --> 01:32:08.495
But that's my only question.

1114
01:32:10.412 --> 01:32:12.995
I haven't thought about it.

1115
01:32:13.287 --> 01:32:15.995
You shouldn't have to think.

1116
01:32:21.912 --> 01:32:22.995
I can't say.

1117
01:32:36.162 --> 01:32:39.745
I do my best
to get by every day.

1118
01:32:40.287 --> 01:32:44.995
There were hard times,
but I wasn't miserable.


1119
01:32:45.912 --> 01:32:49.578
Objectively speaking,
I must be very happy.


1120
01:32:51.037 --> 01:32:56.828
I feel I'd get scolded
if I say I'm not happy.


1121
01:32:57.662 --> 01:33:00.245
I'm asking what you think.

1122
01:33:02.662 --> 01:33:03.870
I don't know...

1123
01:33:10.787 --> 01:33:12.745
Are you happy?

1124
01:33:14.037 --> 01:33:15.703
I'm not.

1125
01:33:15.870 --> 01:33:18.495
Why? Because of your job?

1126
01:33:18.912 --> 01:33:19.828
No.

1127
01:33:21.287 --> 01:33:27.703
Because I've been regretting
not fighting for my feelings.


1128
01:33:28.745 --> 01:33:33.245
I shouldn't have given up,
even if the result was the same.


1129
01:33:33.787 --> 01:33:35.703
But I was ignorant then.

1130
01:33:36.162 --> 01:33:38.495
I was scared to be hurt more.

1131
01:33:39.037 --> 01:33:41.870
That's why I came here to see you.

1132
01:33:42.037 --> 01:33:42.953
Hold on.

1133
01:33:48.037 --> 01:33:53.120
Let me clarify 'cause this conversation
seems important to you.


1134
01:33:53.662 --> 01:33:54.495
What?

1135
01:33:55.912 --> 01:34:00.953
To be honest,
I can't remember your name.


1136
01:34:02.287 --> 01:34:04.203
Are you serious?

1137
01:34:04.412 --> 01:34:09.203
I'm sorry. I hoped I'd recall,
or you'd say it as we talked.


1138
01:34:10.287 --> 01:34:12.620
How could you forget?

1139
01:34:13.412 --> 01:34:15.328
Then it made me wonder.

1140
01:34:15.912 --> 01:34:16.828
What?

1141
01:34:17.162 --> 01:34:19.828
Do you know my name?

1142
01:34:20.412 --> 01:34:21.995
Of course, I do.

1143
01:34:22.245 --> 01:34:24.203
Then who am I?

1144
01:34:26.537 --> 01:34:27.995
Mika Yuki.

1145
01:34:28.162 --> 01:34:29.120
Oh...

1146
01:34:30.912 --> 01:34:31.995
Aya Kobayashi.

1147
01:34:35.620 --> 01:34:37.870
My name's Aya Kobayashi.

1148
01:34:42.287 --> 01:34:46.495
My maiden name's Nomura.
I'm not Mika Yuki either way.


1149
01:34:47.620 --> 01:34:49.703
- You're not Mika?
- No.


1150
01:34:50.162 --> 01:34:53.745
I'm Aya Kobayashi,
and not your classmate.


1151
01:34:54.162 --> 01:34:56.495
You got the wrong person.

1152
01:34:57.412 --> 01:35:01.620
But...you remembered me.

1153
01:35:02.495 --> 01:35:03.828
Well...

1154
01:35:07.662 --> 01:35:10.203
We met on the escalator, right?

1155
01:35:10.662 --> 01:35:11.495
Yeah.

1156
01:35:13.162 --> 01:35:18.995
When we passed each other,
you looked at me all surprised.


1157
01:35:20.495 --> 01:35:25.203
So I thought you
must be someone I know.

1158
01:35:25.787 --> 01:35:31.078
When I went back up, you came down,
and I panicked.


1159
01:35:31.537 --> 01:35:35.245
I was trying hard to recollect.
Then it hit me.


1160
01:35:36.287 --> 01:35:40.203
"She's my classmate
that went to Tokyo for college."


1161
01:35:40.495 --> 01:35:43.370
Doesn't that mean you know me?

1162
01:35:43.620 --> 01:35:45.370
Where's your school?

1163
01:35:45.787 --> 01:35:47.370
Miyagi Girls' High.

1164
01:35:47.912 --> 01:35:49.620
I went to Sendai High.

1165
01:35:53.662 --> 01:35:58.870
See? I'm sorry, it was my mistake.

1166
01:35:59.537 --> 01:36:01.995
I mean, <i>our</i> mistake.

1167
01:36:03.162 --> 01:36:05.370
I don't believe this...

1168
01:36:06.412 --> 01:36:10.953
You must've wanted to see her badly.

1169
01:36:13.162 --> 01:36:15.703
Yes, that's right.

1170
01:36:17.745 --> 01:36:19.453
I missed her so much.

1171
01:36:20.912 --> 01:36:27.245
That must be why you mistook me,
with similar age, for Mika.


1172
01:36:29.912 --> 01:36:31.620
That can't be.

1173
01:36:32.537 --> 01:36:34.953
But you haven't seen her 20 years.

1174
01:36:39.537 --> 01:36:41.453
Did you keep in touch?

1175
01:36:42.495 --> 01:36:43.578
No.

1176
01:36:45.037 --> 01:36:48.245
Cause I heard
she married after college.


1177
01:36:50.745 --> 01:36:54.578
Could it be that
you and Mika were lovers?


1178
01:37:04.162 --> 01:37:05.120
I'm sorry.

1179
01:37:10.787 --> 01:37:11.953
Whoa, excuse me.

1180
01:37:12.120 --> 01:37:14.120
I brought your package.

1181
01:37:15.912 --> 01:37:16.995
Thank you.

1182
01:37:17.287 --> 01:37:19.370
Please sign here.

1183
01:37:19.537 --> 01:37:20.578
Sure.

1184
01:37:24.662 --> 01:37:25.870
<i>Kobayashi</i>

1185
01:37:27.120 --> 01:37:29.578
- Here you go.
- Thank you.


1186
01:37:40.287 --> 01:37:42.245
Why don't you stay longer?

1187
01:37:43.370 --> 01:37:46.370
The sweet bean jelly and kettle's ready.

1188
01:38:37.162 --> 01:38:39.620
It's like a sweet bean popsicle!

1189
01:38:39.787 --> 01:38:40.620
Right?

1190
01:38:41.537 --> 01:38:43.453
A high-grade version.

1191
01:38:49.162 --> 01:38:51.495
Are you sure you're not Mika?

1192
01:38:52.162 --> 01:38:54.620
I'm not Mika. Sorry.

1193
01:38:55.495 --> 01:38:57.620
Ugh.

1194
01:39:03.495 --> 01:39:05.953
Was Mika your first love?

1195
01:39:08.370 --> 01:39:10.328
I'm not sure about that.

1196
01:39:11.370 --> 01:39:13.495
But she was my first partner.

1197
01:39:17.912 --> 01:39:20.245
We dated at the end of high school

1198
01:39:20.537 --> 01:39:24.120
and did long-distance
after I moved to Tokyo.


1199
01:39:24.370 --> 01:39:26.995
Then, she got a boyfriend.

1200
01:39:27.370 --> 01:39:28.245
Oh...

1201
01:39:29.537 --> 01:39:33.370
She wasn't like me,
so I should've seen it coming.


1202
01:39:33.912 --> 01:39:36.495
But I was oblivious somehow.

1203
01:39:36.745 --> 01:39:40.995
You mean, only you
were a genuine lesbian?


1204
01:39:41.162 --> 01:39:42.245
Genuine?

1205
01:39:43.412 --> 01:39:44.328
Yeah.

1206
01:39:45.745 --> 01:39:51.495
We were planning to live together
in Tokyo after college.


1207
01:39:52.120 --> 01:39:55.870
But broke up when she cheated...
I mean, changed.


1208
01:39:56.662 --> 01:39:57.620
I see.

1209
01:39:58.787 --> 01:39:59.995
Never saw her again?

1210
01:40:00.245 --> 01:40:04.370
Yeah. Afterward, someone
told me she married the guy.


1211
01:40:05.537 --> 01:40:07.453
Did you love her?

1212
01:40:19.162 --> 01:40:20.245
My husband...

1213
01:40:23.120 --> 01:40:25.953
He was contacting his high school ex.

1214
01:40:26.120 --> 01:40:27.120
Really?

1215
01:40:29.120 --> 01:40:34.370
I found out because the virus
sent his emails to me.


1216
01:40:35.787 --> 01:40:40.245
You know, you can see
the history of their responses.


1217
01:40:40.412 --> 01:40:41.245
Yeah.

1218
01:40:42.995 --> 01:40:49.745
He wrote in the email, "I really
want to see you, but we shouldn't."


1219
01:40:51.037 --> 01:40:53.995
"I know we love our families."

1220
01:40:54.412 --> 01:40:55.495
He's faithful.

1221
01:40:56.495 --> 01:40:57.453
He is.

1222
01:40:57.870 --> 01:40:59.328
How did you feel?

1223
01:41:02.370 --> 01:41:06.245
It's hard to put it into words.

1224
01:41:07.662 --> 01:41:10.203
But it was beautifully written.

1225
01:41:11.870 --> 01:41:13.870
I was surprised by his words.

1226
01:41:14.287 --> 01:41:15.245
What words?

1227
01:41:21.495 --> 01:41:27.245
"The things you said to me
keeps me going even now."


1228
01:41:30.370 --> 01:41:35.745
"Your existence is my anchor,
even to this day."


1229
01:41:37.245 --> 01:41:43.703
"Meeting you was one of the best things
that has ever happened in my life."


1230
01:41:44.162 --> 01:41:45.495
Wow.

1231
01:41:47.245 --> 01:41:48.745
I kept rereading it.

1232
01:41:50.120 --> 01:41:53.495
But isn't there only one "best thing"?

1233
01:41:53.995 --> 01:41:56.745
Yeah, it's a weird expression.

1234
01:41:57.037 --> 01:41:59.578
Did you tell him you read it?

1235
01:42:00.037 --> 01:42:00.995
No.

1236
01:42:01.287 --> 01:42:04.870
Did your partner...
I mean, Mr. Husband notice?


1237
01:42:05.037 --> 01:42:06.203
"Mr. Husband"?

1238
01:42:07.912 --> 01:42:11.953
I'm not sure.
I think he was too busy back then.


1239
01:42:12.537 --> 01:42:16.453
Almost everything was leaked.

1240
01:42:17.037 --> 01:42:20.328
I bet he couldn't tell what got exposed.

1241
01:42:22.412 --> 01:42:23.870
Not gonna tell him?

1242
01:42:25.662 --> 01:42:28.870
It'll only make things awkward.

1243
01:42:31.287 --> 01:42:34.870
He did contact her, after all.

1244
01:42:36.120 --> 01:42:38.953
And wanted to see her.

1245
01:42:39.412 --> 01:42:40.745
Can't forgive him?

1246
01:42:42.620 --> 01:42:44.245
For just the thought?

1247
01:42:50.995 --> 01:42:55.370
I think you can't stop
wanting to see someone.


1248
01:42:55.787 --> 01:42:58.620
You don't have to be so understanding.

1249
01:43:02.412 --> 01:43:05.953
Sorry. I don't even know you.

1250
01:43:07.912 --> 01:43:08.870
It's okay.

1251
01:43:12.620 --> 01:43:15.078
Do I look understanding?

1252
01:43:21.870 --> 01:43:22.745
What's wrong?

1253
01:43:23.620 --> 01:43:25.828
I keep seeing Mika in you.

1254
01:43:27.287 --> 01:43:29.370
Do I resemble her that much?

1255
01:43:29.620 --> 01:43:32.745
Maybe it's the vibe you give off.

1256
01:43:33.537 --> 01:43:38.245
You look exactly like
what I imagined she'd look now.


1257
01:43:38.495 --> 01:43:40.870
Was Mika understanding?

1258
01:43:41.037 --> 01:43:42.120
Not at all.

1259
01:43:43.870 --> 01:43:48.078
She looks it,
but you can't reason with her.


1260
01:43:48.370 --> 01:43:50.453
Maybe she's really like me.

1261
01:43:58.120 --> 01:44:01.120
I can play Mika if you'd like.

1262
01:44:01.662 --> 01:44:02.745
Play her?

1263
01:44:04.162 --> 01:44:07.370
It seems like a waste.

1264
01:44:07.537 --> 01:44:08.620
Of what?

1265
01:44:08.870 --> 01:44:10.745
The dramatic meeting.

1266
01:44:11.495 --> 01:44:12.953
What do you mean?

1267
01:44:13.162 --> 01:44:15.745
My looks and personality seem to fit.

1268
01:44:15.912 --> 01:44:19.495
- That's not the point.
- I may not be good enough.


1269
01:44:20.787 --> 01:44:26.370
But I know it's something
that means a lot to you.


1270
01:44:32.912 --> 01:44:36.453
I know it's late,
but can I ask your name?


1271
01:44:40.912 --> 01:44:42.328
Natsuko Higuchi.

1272
01:44:43.620 --> 01:44:45.620
Natsuko means "summer child."

1273
01:44:46.537 --> 01:44:47.495
Natsuko.

1274
01:44:48.287 --> 01:44:49.370
Lovely name.

1275
01:45:00.370 --> 01:45:01.495
Natsuko...

1276
01:45:02.537 --> 01:45:04.995
You said you weren't happy.

1277
01:45:06.495 --> 01:45:09.745
Is it my fault?

1278
01:45:10.245 --> 01:45:12.828
Stop it...

1279
01:45:14.537 --> 01:45:17.745
You didn't date anyone after me?

1280
01:45:19.287 --> 01:45:20.828
There were some.

1281
01:45:21.995 --> 01:45:24.078
But I couldn't truly connect.

1282
01:45:24.287 --> 01:45:26.870
Were you truly connected with me?

1283
01:45:31.870 --> 01:45:32.995
Are you mad?

1284
01:45:35.370 --> 01:45:36.120
Yeah.

1285
01:45:39.745 --> 01:45:40.870
I'm mad.

1286
01:45:44.537 --> 01:45:45.703
I'm sorry.

1287
01:45:48.120 --> 01:45:49.453
Don't be.

1288
01:45:50.495 --> 01:45:51.870
It's not you.

1289
01:45:53.120 --> 01:45:56.370
I'm mad I didn't say
the things I should've.


1290
01:45:58.662 --> 01:46:00.245
Like what?

1291
01:46:01.412 --> 01:46:02.828
What I couldn't say.

1292
01:46:04.662 --> 01:46:10.745
When you gave me your last call,
I was at Shibuya Center-gai.


1293
01:46:11.537 --> 01:46:16.870
The trending song and
deeply tanned girls were real noisy.


1294
01:46:19.787 --> 01:46:23.995
But I could hear your voice clearly.

1295
01:46:25.037 --> 01:46:27.745
You sounded determined.

1296
01:46:28.995 --> 01:46:34.245
I sensed you had suffered enough
before you made the call.


1297
01:46:35.287 --> 01:46:38.495
So, I couldn't say anything.

1298
01:46:39.662 --> 01:46:44.328
I knew if I did, it would only
make you suffer more.


1299
01:46:45.537 --> 01:46:50.370
That's why I hung up
and never called again.


1300
01:46:52.537 --> 01:46:55.078
But I wanted to say was

1301
01:46:56.037 --> 01:46:59.620
you're my one and only love.

1302
01:47:05.120 --> 01:47:08.078
You may be able to love someone else,

1303
01:47:08.870 --> 01:47:11.120
but I can't love anyone else.

1304
01:47:14.537 --> 01:47:20.120
Being together with me
may complicate your life.


1305
01:47:21.162 --> 01:47:23.828
But I wanted you to choose me.

1306
01:47:25.037 --> 01:47:26.745
I couldn't say that.

1307
01:47:28.162 --> 01:47:28.995
I see.

1308
01:47:30.662 --> 01:47:36.495
But I didn't come here because
I wanted something from you.


1309
01:47:37.745 --> 01:47:42.620
I just wanted to tell you
that I couldn't say those words.


1310
01:47:43.912 --> 01:47:47.453
Even if it made you suffer,
I should've said it.


1311
01:47:48.245 --> 01:47:53.078
I know now, the pain
was essential for our lives.


1312
01:47:54.287 --> 01:48:01.245
I assumed you'd have a hole
in your life now, just like me.


1313
01:48:02.495 --> 01:48:03.578
So I came.

1314
01:48:05.287 --> 01:48:06.245
A hole?

1315
01:48:08.287 --> 01:48:12.995
You must have a hole
that nothing can fill in.


1316
01:48:16.787 --> 01:48:19.370
There's no way for me to fill it.

1317
01:48:20.745 --> 01:48:23.495
But I have the same hole as you.

1318
01:48:24.495 --> 01:48:30.078
We may be still connected
through that hole.


1319
01:48:31.412 --> 01:48:33.245
I came to tell you that.

1320
01:48:45.662 --> 01:48:46.578
I'm home.

1321
01:48:53.245 --> 01:48:53.995
Is it here?

1322
01:49:02.912 --> 01:49:04.078
Say hello.

1323
01:49:05.162 --> 01:49:05.953
Hello.

1324
01:49:06.662 --> 01:49:08.078
Nice to meet you.

1325
01:49:18.537 --> 01:49:19.703
He's handsome.

1326
01:49:21.787 --> 01:49:23.870
I thought he'd be a geek.

1327
01:49:25.162 --> 01:49:28.495
He can't even say hello.

1328
01:49:31.995 --> 01:49:33.328
I should be going.

1329
01:49:33.537 --> 01:49:36.120
It's okay. He won't come down.

1330
01:49:36.620 --> 01:49:39.620
Your daughter will be back. I'm going.

1331
01:49:40.120 --> 01:49:43.620
Okay. Can I walk you to the station?

1332
01:49:44.370 --> 01:49:46.620
Yeah. Thanks.

1333
01:49:50.537 --> 01:49:55.453
Kei, I'm going to walk
my friend to the station.


1334
01:50:09.120 --> 01:50:11.745
So your son's name is Kei.

1335
01:50:12.037 --> 01:50:12.953
Yeah.

1336
01:50:13.495 --> 01:50:14.745
And the girl's Yu.

1337
01:50:14.995 --> 01:50:15.745
Right.

1338
01:50:16.912 --> 01:50:17.995
How'd you know?

1339
01:50:18.162 --> 01:50:19.870
You mentioned it.

1340
01:50:20.287 --> 01:50:21.328
Oh, yeah.

1341
01:50:21.912 --> 01:50:24.203
Yu means "to play."

1342
01:50:24.787 --> 01:50:26.203
Nice, simple names.

1343
01:50:26.412 --> 01:50:32.870
We wanted gender-neutral names
so it wouldn't shackle them later.


1344
01:50:33.037 --> 01:50:34.620
You're progressive.

1345
01:50:35.787 --> 01:50:37.620
What's Mr. Husband like?

1346
01:50:40.662 --> 01:50:43.495
He's a steady, diligent person.

1347
01:50:44.037 --> 01:50:45.995
That might be the best.

1348
01:50:46.162 --> 01:50:49.120
- You think so?
- Well, I don't know him.


1349
01:50:49.287 --> 01:50:53.495
But I felt trust and a little distance
from your tone.


1350
01:50:54.912 --> 01:50:55.995
You're right.

1351
01:50:57.037 --> 01:50:59.495
- But you missed "love."
- Sorry.


1352
01:50:59.912 --> 01:51:00.828
It's okay.

1353
01:51:02.245 --> 01:51:04.495
I've never told anyone before.

1354
01:51:05.120 --> 01:51:06.370
I'm honored.

1355
01:51:07.412 --> 01:51:08.703
I'm amazed.

1356
01:51:18.912 --> 01:51:19.703
What is it?

1357
01:51:20.245 --> 01:51:23.370
Who did you mistake me for?

1358
01:51:24.620 --> 01:51:28.370
She was my high school classmate.
A boyish girl.


1359
01:51:28.662 --> 01:51:30.328
Were you two close?

1360
01:51:30.537 --> 01:51:34.620
Not really. We weren't that close.

1361
01:51:36.162 --> 01:51:40.370
She often played the piano
alone at lunch break.


1362
01:51:40.787 --> 01:51:44.495
I also played the piano as a hobby.

1363
01:51:45.162 --> 01:51:48.745
So we started meeting
in the music room at lunch.


1364
01:51:49.620 --> 01:51:54.120
We took turns playing the piano
during lunch break


1365
01:51:54.662 --> 01:51:57.745
and ate listening to each other's piano.

1366
01:51:58.662 --> 01:52:03.120
We didn't talk in class.
Only in the music room.


1367
01:52:03.287 --> 01:52:05.578
- What a lovely memory.
- Yeah.


1368
01:52:06.037 --> 01:52:07.828
It was sort of special.

1369
01:52:08.787 --> 01:52:11.620
We lost contact after she went to Tokyo.

1370
01:52:15.162 --> 01:52:22.120
<i>Sendai Station</i>

1371
01:52:23.787 --> 01:52:24.620
Hey.

1372
01:52:26.287 --> 01:52:28.370
Let's play pretend again.

1373
01:52:29.370 --> 01:52:30.953
Where should we start?

1374
01:52:31.120 --> 01:52:35.453
I'll be your boyish pianist this time.

1375
01:52:35.662 --> 01:52:37.370
But my memory's hazy.

1376
01:52:37.537 --> 01:52:39.995
- It seems unfair.
- Why?


1377
01:52:40.162 --> 01:52:41.203
Let me do it!

1378
01:52:43.037 --> 01:52:45.245
All right. You walk from there.

1379
01:52:45.412 --> 01:52:48.953
We meet when I come up
the escalator, okay?


1380
01:52:49.120 --> 01:52:50.245
It's like a skit.

1381
01:53:28.662 --> 01:53:29.495
Aya?

1382
01:53:31.412 --> 01:53:32.620
Is it you?

1383
01:53:34.620 --> 01:53:36.828
Do you recognize me?

1384
01:53:37.412 --> 01:53:39.328
Yeah, from high school.

1385
01:53:40.162 --> 01:53:42.620
But I can't remember your name.

1386
01:53:42.787 --> 01:53:44.328
It doesn't matter.

1387
01:53:44.912 --> 01:53:47.620
Remember playing the piano together?

1388
01:53:47.787 --> 01:53:48.703
Of course.

1389
01:53:49.245 --> 01:53:51.703
Why are you back from Tokyo?

1390
01:53:52.537 --> 01:53:55.495
For the reunion. 
I'm on my way back.

1391
01:53:55.662 --> 01:53:58.245
Why were you invited, but not me?

1392
01:53:58.412 --> 01:54:00.245
Who knows?

1393
01:54:01.245 --> 01:54:05.995
But I'm glad to see you.
I was wondering how you were doing.


1394
01:54:06.370 --> 01:54:07.370
You mean it?

1395
01:54:08.120 --> 01:54:08.995
I do.

1396
01:54:09.412 --> 01:54:14.495
I'm glad. I thought no one from
high school would remember me.


1397
01:54:14.662 --> 01:54:19.245
No way. I was secretly proud
that I could talk with you.


1398
01:54:19.620 --> 01:54:21.203
- You were?
- Yeah.


1399
01:54:21.870 --> 01:54:27.120
You gave off an antisocial vibe,
but many wanted to talk to you.


1400
01:54:27.620 --> 01:54:29.370
- Are you sure?
- I am.


1401
01:54:29.745 --> 01:54:31.370
You were admired.

1402
01:54:31.662 --> 01:54:34.495
Cut it out. You're gonna make me cry.

1403
01:54:37.787 --> 01:54:39.078
How are you doing?

1404
01:54:39.245 --> 01:54:44.120
Good. There are struggles,
but I live every day to the fullest.


1405
01:54:44.412 --> 01:54:47.620
I'm so glad you haven't changed.

1406
01:54:48.162 --> 01:54:50.078
And you? Are you good?

1407
01:54:51.787 --> 01:54:55.578
I can't answer straight away like you.

1408
01:54:55.787 --> 01:54:57.120
You're not well?

1409
01:54:57.495 --> 01:54:59.370
- My body's fine.
- Then...


1410
01:55:00.537 --> 01:55:03.078
It's not a big problem.

1411
01:55:03.995 --> 01:55:08.703
But sometimes I wonder why I'm here.

1412
01:55:12.162 --> 01:55:17.245
I could've become anything,
but time flew past before I knew.


1413
01:55:18.662 --> 01:55:20.245
I'm fairly satisfied.

1414
01:55:21.662 --> 01:55:23.870
This is what I chose.

1415
01:55:24.870 --> 01:55:27.953
And I know it's wrong to want more.

1416
01:55:30.162 --> 01:55:30.995
But...

1417
01:55:35.412 --> 01:55:39.745
I'm not passionate
about anything anymore.


1418
01:55:43.037 --> 01:55:44.870
I don't know what to do.

1419
01:55:46.370 --> 01:55:47.328
Time is...

1420
01:55:48.537 --> 01:55:50.370
slowly killing me.

1421
01:55:58.245 --> 01:56:01.120
I'm sorry to say
this all of a sudden.

1422
01:56:02.162 --> 01:56:02.995
It's okay.

1423
01:56:05.537 --> 01:56:08.620
Can I tell you how
I saw you back then?

1424
01:56:10.037 --> 01:56:10.828
Sure.

1425
01:56:12.162 --> 01:56:16.995
You said everyone admired me,
but that's wrong.


1426
01:56:17.537 --> 01:56:22.995
I always felt different,
like everyone observed me from afar.


1427
01:56:24.412 --> 01:56:27.953
I always felt like an outcast.

1428
01:56:29.370 --> 01:56:32.370
You were the only one that stepped in.

1429
01:56:32.912 --> 01:56:36.828
It was just one step,
but it meant a lot to me.


1430
01:56:37.620 --> 01:56:43.328
You were the only light for me.
I could find you anywhere you were.


1431
01:56:46.120 --> 01:56:49.328
Your existence gave me power.

1432
01:56:50.287 --> 01:56:51.245
It's true.

1433
01:56:51.412 --> 01:56:55.370
You have the ability
to give people power.


1434
01:56:55.537 --> 01:56:57.203
Please remember that.

1435
01:56:59.745 --> 01:57:00.495
Thanks.

1436
01:57:02.662 --> 01:57:06.995
But I didn't say <i>everyone</i> admired you.

1437
01:57:07.287 --> 01:57:08.078
Huh?

1438
01:57:08.662 --> 01:57:10.870
I admired you.

1439
01:57:17.995 --> 01:57:18.953
Thank you.

1440
01:57:23.037 --> 01:57:24.620
I'm glad I met you.

1441
01:57:26.287 --> 01:57:28.953
I'm glad I met you, too.

1442
01:57:33.162 --> 01:57:33.870
Bye.

1443
01:57:35.287 --> 01:57:36.078
See you!

1444
01:57:37.662 --> 01:57:38.370
See you.

1445
01:58:52.787 --> 01:58:54.120
- Wait.
- What's wrong?


1446
01:58:55.787 --> 01:58:58.370
- It's nothing big.
- What is it?


1447
01:58:58.995 --> 01:59:01.245
But I can only tell you.

1448
01:59:01.412 --> 01:59:02.745
Tell me anything.

1449
01:59:03.412 --> 01:59:05.245
- I remembered.
- What?


1450
01:59:05.412 --> 01:59:06.370
Her name.

1451
01:59:08.620 --> 01:59:09.995
It's Nozomi.

1452
01:59:10.745 --> 01:59:11.703
Nozomi?

1453
01:59:14.370 --> 01:59:16.078
- Nozomi!
- Nozomi!


1454
01:59:19.412 --> 01:59:20.370
And her surname?

1455
01:59:20.787 --> 01:59:21.995
Can't remember.

